00:00:11.052 --> 00:00:12.887 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA]
Don't twist my words!

00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.973 position:50% align:center
I meant, I need space
for today, yeah? Today.

00:00:15.056 --> 00:00:18.226 position:50% align:center
--Whoa.
--Guess somebody's arguing.

00:00:18.309 --> 00:00:19.894 position:50% align:center
What's the matter?

00:00:21.062 --> 00:00:22.439 position:50% align:center
Hirano.

00:00:22.522 --> 00:00:24.607 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO] Why haven't
you guys gone home yet?

00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:27.152 position:50% align:center
Apparently, he's in a fight
with his girlfriend again.

00:00:27.235 --> 00:00:29.237 position:50% align:center
Fudanshi! Just the guy I need!

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:30.280 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:00:30.363 --> 00:00:31.865 position:50% align:center
Since you're fluent in fujoshi!

00:00:31.948 --> 00:00:33.366 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
I'm what?

00:00:35.118 --> 00:00:38.163 position:50% align:center
Uh, hi. Fudanshi speaking.

00:00:39.289 --> 00:00:42.000 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA] What do you think
about delinquent ukes?

00:00:42.083 --> 00:00:43.376 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Huh?

00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:44.961 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA] The type who thinks
he's too cool for school

00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:47.714 position:50% align:center
and puts on a big macho act
when the seme's around.

00:00:47.797 --> 00:00:49.049 position:50% align:center
But as soon as they're
alone together,

00:00:49.132 --> 00:00:50.633 position:50% align:center
he's taken completely off-guard

00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:52.927 position:50% align:center
by the stronger and
more assertive seme,

00:00:53.011 --> 00:00:54.971 position:50% align:center
and though his words
are shy and reluctant,

00:00:55.055 --> 00:00:57.349 position:50% align:center
his body knows
exactly what it wants.

00:00:57.432 --> 00:00:59.517 position:50% align:center
The next day, the seme acts
all cool and unbothered,

00:00:59.601 --> 00:01:00.769 position:50% align:center
showing that he's
got the upper hand

00:01:00.852 --> 00:01:02.270 position:50% align:center
in their relationship again,

00:01:02.354 --> 00:01:04.773 position:50% align:center
but he's hopelessly bound
to the object of his affection.

00:01:04.856 --> 00:01:08.026 position:50% align:center
That's what makes for a
compelling delinquent uke!

00:01:08.109 --> 00:01:10.362 position:50% align:center
So do you like that?

00:01:10.445 --> 00:01:11.988 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
I like that.

00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:13.114 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Mya...

00:01:13.198 --> 00:01:14.157 position:50% align:center
Listen here, punk,
you'd better not be

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:15.116 position:50% align:center
flirting with my girlfriend!

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:16.284 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
No, of course I wasn't!

00:01:16.368 --> 00:01:17.285 position:50% align:center
She was just explaining

00:01:17.369 --> 00:01:19.120 position:50% align:center
delinquent ukes
to me, that's all!

00:01:19.204 --> 00:01:20.872 position:50% align:center
Let me listen in, too.

00:01:23.416 --> 00:01:25.877 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA] Is it me,
or have they gotten super close?

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:29.422 position:50% align:center
Huh? Why do you think
I'd have the answer to that?

00:01:29.506 --> 00:01:31.466 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA]
Sasaki's enjoying this.

00:01:31.549 --> 00:01:33.468 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA] I mean, of course
I like delinquent ukes.

00:01:33.551 --> 00:01:34.678 position:50% align:center
Like who wouldn't?

00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:36.680 position:50% align:center
But it wasn't 'til
I started dating Jiro...

00:01:36.763 --> 00:01:37.555 position:50% align:center
Jiro?

00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:39.265 position:50% align:center
Ogasawara's first name.

00:01:39.349 --> 00:01:41.059 position:50% align:center
Aha.

00:01:41.142 --> 00:01:43.061 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA] Him being a delinquent
is just a coincidence.

00:01:43.144 --> 00:01:44.145 position:50% align:center
That's it, end of story!

00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:46.356 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI, MIYANO]
She never stops talking.

00:01:46.439 --> 00:01:48.650 position:50% align:center
Hey, put it on speaker
so I can hear, too.

00:01:48.733 --> 00:01:51.194 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA]
...obsessing over that stuff.

00:01:51.277 --> 00:01:52.779 position:50% align:center
Jiro is such an idiot!

00:01:52.862 --> 00:01:54.155 position:50% align:center
What did you say?

00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:56.199 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA]
Seriously! Why did you suddenly

00:01:56.282 --> 00:01:58.368 position:50% align:center
ask for space out of nowhere?

00:01:58.451 --> 00:01:59.744 position:50% align:center
I think you know.

00:01:59.828 --> 00:02:00.912 position:50% align:center
Because of that manga
that you were

00:02:00.995 --> 00:02:02.580 position:50% align:center
hiding in your photo albums!

00:02:02.664 --> 00:02:05.166 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA gasps]
Why would you open it?

00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:07.752 position:50% align:center
I hid it in there so you
wouldn't get your feelings hurt!

00:02:07.836 --> 00:02:09.421 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA] But that just
made me suspicious!

00:02:09.504 --> 00:02:11.006 position:50% align:center
I mean, the main characters
were a delinquent...

00:02:11.089 --> 00:02:13.508 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] Why doesn't he
take it off speaker?

00:02:13.591 --> 00:02:16.678 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] This is pretty typical
for those two, actually.

00:02:16.761 --> 00:02:18.388 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
They sure are passionate.

00:02:18.471 --> 00:02:20.390 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
It's because they're so close.

00:02:20.473 --> 00:02:22.517 position:50% align:center
Happens every
couple weeks or so.

00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:24.227 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Well, when the storm clears.

00:02:24.310 --> 00:02:26.896 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
Oh, it's still coming down.

00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:28.148 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA]
And when your lover's tentacles

00:02:28.231 --> 00:02:29.691 position:50% align:center
are feverishly embracing you,

00:02:29.774 --> 00:02:30.942 position:50% align:center
who needs words anyway?

00:02:31.026 --> 00:02:32.527 position:50% align:center
Whoa. You're on speaker!

00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:34.904 position:50% align:center
You really think it's okay
to yell stuff like that?

00:02:34.988 --> 00:02:37.532 position:50% align:center
Hang on. Back me
up here, fudanshi.

00:02:37.615 --> 00:02:39.200 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's a bit too much.

00:02:39.284 --> 00:02:42.162 position:50% align:center
Even he thinks so!
Have some manners, why don't ya?

00:02:42.245 --> 00:02:45.123 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA] Oh my god.
You are the worst, Jiro.

00:02:45.206 --> 00:02:46.958 position:50% align:center
Why does your
timing always suck?

00:02:47.042 --> 00:02:49.294 position:50% align:center
Having this discussion over
the phone is getting us nowhere.

00:02:49.377 --> 00:02:50.462 position:50% align:center
Stay put. I'm coming to

00:02:50.545 --> 00:02:52.922 position:50% align:center
set the record straight
once and for all!

00:02:53.006 --> 00:02:54.549 position:50% align:center
Like, right now?

00:02:54.632 --> 00:02:56.634 position:50% align:center
Oh and look at that.
She hung up on me.

00:02:56.718 --> 00:02:58.094 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
She's coming here?

00:02:58.178 --> 00:03:01.598 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA] Yeah. She goes to
the co-ed school nearby.

00:03:01.681 --> 00:03:05.643 position:50% align:center
Then it should only be
about ten minutes. What is it?

00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:06.478 position:50% align:center
Uh, nothing, sorry.

00:03:06.561 --> 00:03:08.104 position:50% align:center
I gotta get going. See ya!

00:03:08.188 --> 00:03:09.689 position:50% align:center
Hey, no running.

00:03:09.773 --> 00:03:12.233 position:50% align:center
Are you gonna let her control
your life after you're married?

00:03:12.317 --> 00:03:14.986 position:50% align:center
Oh, you guys are
getting married?

00:03:15.070 --> 00:03:17.030 position:50% align:center
If I don't see myself
marrying her,

00:03:17.113 --> 00:03:18.615 position:50% align:center
then why would I date her?

00:03:18.698 --> 00:03:20.158 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:03:20.241 --> 00:03:23.286 position:50% align:center
I bet your girlfriend really
likes that about you, Ogasawara.

00:03:23.370 --> 00:03:25.580 position:50% align:center
I can't tell if you guys
are messing with me!

00:03:28.792 --> 00:03:30.710 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA gasps]
Eimi!

00:03:32.295 --> 00:03:33.213 position:50% align:center
[YOKODA]
Hmph!

00:03:34.798 --> 00:03:36.675 position:50% align:center
[OGASAWARA]
Look, I'm sorry.

00:03:37.967 --> 00:03:40.178 position:50% align:center
Hashtag life goals.

00:03:40.261 --> 00:03:42.555 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
I'm headed this way. See ya.

00:03:42.639 --> 00:03:43.932 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Goodbye, Hirano.

00:03:44.015 --> 00:03:45.892 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Bye-bye.

00:03:45.975 --> 00:03:48.144 position:50% align:center
Whatcha say, Mya,
you want to hit the bookstore?

00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:49.354 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:53.316 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
You know something?

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:56.611 position:50% align:center
When you and I walk down
the street together like this,

00:03:56.695 --> 00:03:58.947 position:50% align:center
we look like a couple.

00:03:59.030 --> 00:04:03.410 position:50% align:center
Huh? Really? Why is that?

00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:04.828 position:50% align:center
I mean, I would say
we just look like

00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:06.579 position:50% align:center
classmates hanging out
after school.

00:04:06.663 --> 00:04:08.456 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI chuckles]

00:04:18.091 --> 00:04:20.635 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Does it make you self-conscious?

00:04:24.764 --> 00:04:30.603 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] Honestly?
I'm still deciding, so kind of.

00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:38.153 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Right.

00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:21.089 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA] Miyano. I brought you
an outfit for the competition!

00:06:21.965 --> 00:06:23.883 position:50% align:center
But I have plenty of options.

00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:25.385 position:50% align:center
Sweet.

00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:26.970 position:50% align:center
Is it?

00:06:27.053 --> 00:06:29.597 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA] So, what's your class
doing for the festival?

00:06:29.681 --> 00:06:32.475 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] An escape room.
You have to solve a mystery.

00:06:32.559 --> 00:06:34.310 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA]
Well, doesn't that sound fun?

00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:36.271 position:50% align:center
Maybe I'll come
and check it out.

00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:38.606 position:50% align:center
--[MIYANO] You should!
--[TORIHARA] Miyano!

00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:41.026 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] Sorry, guess that they
need me. I'll be right back.

00:06:41.109 --> 00:06:42.444 position:50% align:center
Of course.

00:06:49.325 --> 00:06:50.910 position:50% align:center
You'll have an outfit
ready to go, too,

00:06:50.994 --> 00:06:52.495 position:50% align:center
in case we need a backup, right?

00:06:52.579 --> 00:06:54.414 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:06:54.497 --> 00:06:57.000 position:50% align:center
[TASHIRO] Here you go, guys!
I went ahead and grabbed

00:06:57.083 --> 00:07:00.587 position:50% align:center
as much cardboard
as I could find. So, uh.

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:04.591 position:50% align:center
Don't just drop it, Tashiro!

00:07:04.674 --> 00:07:07.677 position:50% align:center
Whoa. Hi there,
what's your name?

00:07:10.764 --> 00:07:13.433 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA]
Um, Tasuko Kuresawa.

00:07:14.601 --> 00:07:16.269 position:50% align:center
Oh man, it's Kuresawa!

00:07:16.353 --> 00:07:19.439 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 8B] Dude, I can't
believe you fell for that!

00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:22.233 position:50% align:center
Kuresawa, I got more
black curtains!

00:07:22.317 --> 00:07:23.068 position:50% align:center
What's his problem?

00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:24.194 position:50% align:center
[TASHIRO]
Nothing, okay?

00:07:24.277 --> 00:07:26.029 position:50% align:center
Tashiro saw my outfit
for the festival

00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:27.530 position:50% align:center
and fell for me instantly.

00:07:27.614 --> 00:07:29.074 position:50% align:center
But sadly, our love
wasn't meant to be.

00:07:29.157 --> 00:07:31.701 position:50% align:center
[TASHIRO] Can you at least
not tell the world about it?

00:07:33.787 --> 00:07:35.747 position:50% align:center
Listen, I try not to
turn my friends into BL,

00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:37.832 position:50% align:center
but you gotta stop giving me
all this free material.

00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:39.167 position:50% align:center
It's not me, it's him!

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:41.461 position:50% align:center
I just got caught
in the crossfire!

00:07:41.544 --> 00:07:45.215 position:50% align:center
Hello? Can we do your fitting
after school tomorrow instead?

00:07:45.298 --> 00:07:47.884 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] Sure, that's fine.
Thanks for all your help.

00:07:47.967 --> 00:07:50.053 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA]
My pleasure. Toodle-oo!

00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:56.393 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA] All right,
enough pouting, Tashiro.

00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:58.311 position:50% align:center
Everyone else has moved past it.

00:07:58.395 --> 00:07:59.854 position:50% align:center
[TASHIRO] Please let me
hide from my shame, Kuresawa!

00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:01.856 position:50% align:center
It's time to face the world.

00:08:01.940 --> 00:08:04.859 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO chuckles] So, did your
dress fit you pretty well?

00:08:04.943 --> 00:08:08.196 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Hanzawa's sister is tall.

00:08:08.279 --> 00:08:10.990 position:50% align:center
